4.5. Apply NMSTATE NNCP policies
REF : Chapter 8. Network requirements | Planning your deployment | Red Hat OpenShift Data Foundation | 4.18 | Red Hat Documentation

the logic of having the NNCP policies is to have a MACVLAN interface on which MULTUS is configured for ODF. Now, the MACVLAN can be on top of a single interface or a bonded interface. Additionally, in VVT (Suwon) setups, there is a requirement of having a VLAN interface on top of bond/single interface. So, PLEASE check the network plan and requirements and proceed accordingly. The NNCP YAMLs for all type of configurations are provided below (these are examples, please choose the interface names and IPs correctly).



The different configurations are as below :

 single interface → MACVLAN
 single interface → VLAN → MACVLAN
 two interfaces → bond interface → MACVLAN
 two interfaces → bond interface → VLAN → MACVLAN
